cypher: Quadratic Addition
author: Merle (Marc Wallace)
date:   12 May 93
formal: Cypher quadadd("Quadratic Addition", encode, decode);


choose four random bytes: a, b, c, and d.  store these first.
construct a table arr[x] = (ax^2 + bx + c) mod 256 (char size).
for each input I[x] output (I[x] + arr[x mod d]) mod 256.
to recover data, use the negative of the polynomial.


